Checking for system and security issues.
translations.Server-side encryption makes it possible: Server-side encryption makes it possible to encrypt files which are uploaded to this server. This comes with limitations like a performance penalty, so enable this only if needed.
translations.Please read carefully before activating: Please read carefully before activating server-side encryption:
translations.Once encryption is enabled, all files up: Once encryption is enabled, all files uploaded to the server from that point forward will be encrypted at rest on the server. It will only be possible to disable encryption at a later date if the active encryption module supports that function, and all pre-conditions (e.g. setting a recover key) are met.
translations.Encryption alone does not guarantee secu: Encryption alone does not guarantee complete security. Please read the documentation for information on how the encryption app works, and supported use cases.
translations.Be aware that encryption always increase: Be aware that encryption always increases the file size.
translations.It is always good to create regular back: It is always good to create regular backups of your data, in case of encryption make sure to backup the encryption keys along with your data.
translations.This is the final warning: Do you really: This is the final warning: Do you really want to enable encryption?
translations.No encryption module loaded, please enab: No encryption module loaded, please enable an encryption module in the app menu.
translations.You need to migrate your encryption keys: You need to migrate your encryption keys from the old encryption (ownCloud <= 8.0) to the new one. Please enable the "Default encryption module" and run 'occ encryption:migrate'

translations.It's important for the security and perf: It's important for the security and performance of your instance that everything is configured correctly. To help you with that we are doing some automatic checks. Please see the Tips & Tricks section and the documentation for more information.
translations.PHP does not seem to be setup properly t: PHP does not seem to be setup properly to query system environment variables. The test with getenv("PATH") only returns an empty response.
translations.Please check the <a target=\"_blank\" re: Please check the installation documentation ↗ for PHP configuration notes and the PHP configuration of your server, especially when using php-fpm.
translations.The Read-Only config has been enabled. T: The Read-Only config has been enabled. This prevents setting some configurations via the web-interface. Furthermore, the file needs to be made writable manually for every update.
translations.PHP is apparently set up to strip inline: PHP is apparently set up to strip inline doc blocks. This will make several core apps inaccessible.
translations.This is probably caused by a cache/accel: This is probably caused by a cache/accelerator such as Zend OPcache or eAccelerator.
translations.Your database does not run with \"READ C: Your database does not run with "READ COMMITTED" transaction isolation level. This can cause problems when multiple actions are executed in parallel.
translations.%1$s below version %2$s is installed, fo: %1$s below version %2$s is installed, for stability and performance reasons it is recommended to update to a newer %1$s version.
translations.The PHP module 'fileinfo' is missing. It: The PHP module 'fileinfo' is missing. It is strongly recommended to enable this module to get the best results with MIME type detection.
translations.Transactional file locking is disabled,: Transactional file locking is disabled, this might lead to issues with race conditions. Enable 'filelocking.enabled' in config.php to avoid these problems. See the documentation ↗ for more information.
translations.System locale can not be set to a one wh: System locale can not be set to a one which supports UTF-8.
translations.This means that there might be problems: This means that there might be problems with certain characters in filenames.
translations.It is strongly proposed to install the r: It is strongly proposed to install the required packages on your system to support one of the following locales: %s.
translations.If your installation is not installed at: If your installation is not installed at the root of the domain and uses system cron, there can be issues with the URL generation. To avoid these problems, please set the "overwrite.cli.url" option in your config.php file to the webroot path of your installation (Suggested: "%s")
